definition.value: A formate ester resulting from the formal condensation of formic acid with ethanol.
An ester of formic acid.
A long-chain fatty acid that is icosanoic acid carrying a 3-hydroxy substituent.
A 3-hydroxy fatty acid that is the 3-hydroxy derivative of tetracosanoic (lignoceric) acid.
A long-chain fatty acid that is icosanoic acid in which the hydrogens at the beta-position are replaced by an oxo group.
The 3-oxo monocarboxylic acid which has docasanoic (behenic) acid as the parent acid.
A chlorine oxide that is the chloro derivative of perchloric acid.
A ruthenium coordination entity consisting of ruthenium(II) chloride bound to three 2,2'-bipyridine units.
A ruthenium coordination entity consisting of ruthenium(II) chloride bound to three 4,4'-diphenyl-2,2'-bipyridine units.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups are both oleoyl.
An ortho-fused compound in which at least one of the rings contains at least one heteroatom.
An aromatic ketone in which the keto unit is bound to at least one naphthyl group.
A naphthyl ketone that is naphthalene substituted at position 2 by an acetyl group.
An aldehyde in which the organyl group is a naphthyl group.
A naphthaldehyde with a formyl group at position 1.
A naphthaldehyde that is naphthalene substituted by a formyl group at position 2.
A dihydroceramide in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as 2-hydroxytetracosanoyl.
An N-(2-hydroxyhexacosanoyl)phytosphingosine in which the 4-hydroxy group on the phytosphingosine portion has R-configuration.
An episterol ester obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of  palmitoleic acid with the hydroxy group of episterol.
A hexadecenoyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of hexadec-2-enoic acid.
A nitrometallate anion that consists of six nitro groups covalently bound to a central Pt(2-) species.
A 3beta-sterol that is zymosterol which carries a hyroxymethyl group at position 4.
An anionic coordination entity where nitro groups are coordinated to a metal centre.
An endocannabinoid and an endogenous agonist of the cannabinoid receptors (CB1 and CB2). It is an ester formed from omega-6-arachidonic acid and glycerol.
A sterol ester obtained by formal condensation of the 3-hydroxy group of lanosterol with the carboxy group of any carboxylic acid.
